er, and with them comes a sense of uncertainty with respect to liberal democratic traditions: whether treated as abstractions or concrete realities, cultural divisions challenge concepts of legitimacy and political representation as well as the legal bases for citizenship. Thus, an understanding of such borders and their consequences is of utmost importance for promoting the evolution of democracy. Cultural Borders of Europe provides a wide-ranging exploration of these lines of demarcation in a variety of regions and historical eras, providing essential insights into the state of European intercultural relations today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBorderlandsxPolitical aspectszEurope. 0aBorderlandsxSocial aspectszEurope. 0aCultural pluralismzEurope. 0aDemocracyzEurope. 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectszEurope. 0aLiberalismzEurope. 0aMulticulturalismzEurope. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh1 aAndrén, Mats, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrén, Mats, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBerg, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCornell, Per, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehlen, Fernand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrinell, Klas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJärlehed, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLarsson, Göran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeppänen, Katarina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindkvist, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindkvist, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aL